translated: Dahlgren, Birger Axel Leonard, district medical officer, principal, from Älmhult, born October 10th, 1891 in Växjö. His father was a factor named C.A.E.D and his mother was Aug. Andersson. He married Märta Sandström in 1924, and they had a son named Gunnar born in 1933. He passed his high school exams in 1911, and his teaching exam in 1912. He took a course in oil subjects and traveled to southern Germany in 1922. He was a teacher at the folk school in Kristianopel from 1913-1918, and then at Älmhult from 1918. He became district medical officer in Älmhult in 1932, and principal of a vocational school in 1921. He was Secretary to the commission on intermediate communication from 1920-1922, and then for the building committee for school buildings from 1923-1926. He was chairman of the handicraft association from 1930-1934, and in the election committee from 1925-1945. He was a member of the municipal council, chairman of the committee on poor relief in 1936, vice chairman of the Red Cross district in 1936, chairman of the public library in 1939, vice chairman of the childcare committee, and a member of the municipal board in 1932. He was vice chairman of the church board from 1939-1942, and vice chairman of the school board in 1940. He was awarded the Swedish Order of Vasa in 1946.
